						               													<description>Ushabti are statues used in ancient Egyptian funerals. They were placed in tombs along with other goods to assist the deceased in the afterlife. They came in a number of figures and sizes and provided different benefits in the afterlife.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Place Ushabti in your burial chamber or place them in your sarcophagus in order to gain influence for the afterlife. Have the highest influence for two rounds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player selects one of the cards in their hand to gain influence. This card is placed directly in front of them. This card may be placed in the player&amp;rsquo;s burial chamber so all can see (face up) or placed in the player&amp;rsquo;s sarcophagus (face down). All cards are revealed simultaneously. Each player passes their hand to the neighboring player: alternate passing clockwise and counterclockwise each round. After all the cards have been played, the round ends and the influence is scored.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each card provides influence in up to three ways. Each Ushabti provides a base level of influence and additional influence based on whether it is prominently displayed in the burial chamber. Each Ushabti also provides influence in a unique way, depending on what other types of Ushabti are in each player&amp;rsquo;s burial chamber and/or sarcophagus.&amp;#10;Shuffle and deal new hands to each player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
